Today we'll answer an important business question:

> **"How do we encourage users to keep using the app without becoming annoying?"**

A user who uploads only one report may forget about your app. Smart, helpful notifications can bring them back when they need it.

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, you'll know:

* Which notifications to send
* When to send them
* Which notifications to avoid
* How users should control notifications

---

# Why Notifications Matter

Blood tests are not done every day.

Most people get them:

* Every 3 months
* Every 6 months
* Once a year

Without reminders, users may simply forget to upload their next report.

---

# Types of Notifications

For your MVP, keep notifications simple and useful.

### 1. Report Upload Reminder

Example:

```text
📄 It's been about 6 months since your last blood report.

Upload your latest report to continue tracking your health.
```

---

### 2. OCR Processing Complete

```text
✅ Your blood report has been processed.

Tap to view your AI summary.
```

---

### 3. AI Summary Ready

```text
🩸 Your health summary is ready.

Open the app to review your report.
```

---

### 4. Monthly Health Reminder

```text
📅 No new reports this month.

Remember to upload your next blood report after your next lab test.
```

Only send this if appropriate—not every month for everyone.

---

# Notifications We Should NOT Send

Avoid messages like:

```text
⚠ Your Vitamin D is dangerously low!
```

Or:

```text
You may have diabetes.
```

Notifications appear on the lock screen and may be seen by others. They should never reveal sensitive health details.

---

# Notification Settings

Users should have full control.

Example:

```text
Notifications

☑ Report Upload Reminders

☑ AI Summary Notifications

☑ Product Updates

☐ Marketing Messages
```

For the MVP, don't include marketing messages.

---

# Choosing Reminder Frequency

Don't remind everyone at the same interval.

Instead, let users choose.

Example:

```text
Reminder Frequency

○ Every 3 months

○ Every 6 months

○ Every 12 months

○ No reminders
```

---

# Smart Reminder Logic

Instead of sending reminders based on the installation date:

Use the **date of the last uploaded report**.

Example:

```text
Last Report

15 Jul 2026

↓

Reminder after 6 months

↓

15 Jan 2027
```

This makes reminders much more relevant.

